  "prompt": "Is spot counselling for reserved candidates?",
  "response": "Spot counselling is typically conducted by educational institutions during the admission process, and it can vary by institution and region. Generally, spot counselling is meant to fill vacant seats after the main counselling rounds. While reserved candidates may have specific quotas and provisions, spot counselling may also include opportunities for all candidates, provided they meet certain eligibility criteria.\n\nIn many cases, specific rules about who can participate in spot counselling will be outlined by the institution or the governing body managing the admissions process. It's best to check with the specific institution or the official guidelines related to the counselling process to determine if spot counselling is available for reserved candidates and under what conditions.",
